                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>ذم الفناء</p>
                            <p>A collection of qasidas, bearing the title Dhammu'l-Faná, which (as
                                a must here signify) is equivalent to De contemptu mundi. According
                                to the late Mr E. J. W. Gibb, whose letter accompanies the MS.,
                                this work was composed by a certain Muslihu'd-Dín-oghlu of
                                Sirsirat (probably for Siristad), in Bozqir, a district in the
                                south-west of the vilayet of Qoniya.</p>
                            <p>Begins:</p>
                            <p>ثنا و حمد لا يُحْصَى سما ای خالق فیاض</p>
                            <p>امثال لله سنسن قادر (0) فیاض (قباض)</p>
                            <p>كه يوقدر سكا</p>
                            <p>Ff. 122 of 21 x 15.4 c. and 16 ll. Defective at the end. Poor but
                                legible Turkish naskh. Bought at Kazan by Professor E. H. Minns in
                                September, 1898.</p>
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="W_6-item1">
                            <author key="" cert="medium">
                                <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x">Muslihu'd-Dín-oghlu of Sirsirat</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x" key="">Dhammu'l-Faná</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar" key="">ذم الفناء</title>
                            <note>A collection of qasidas; the title is equivalent to <title
                                    xml:lang="la" key="">De contemptu mundi</title>. Composed, per a
                                letter of the late <persName role="fmo" key="person_137883503">E.
                                    J. W. Gibb</persName> that accompanies the manuscript, in
                                Bozqir, a district in the south-west of the vilayet of
                                Qoniya.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ota">ثنا و حمد لا يُحْصَى سما ای خالق فیاض امثال لله
                                سنسن قادر فیاض كه يوقدر سكا</incipit>
                            <explicit/>
                            <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                        </msItem>
